Jun 8 2009	Absolutely Fabulous	Spent a very glitzy 4 nights at the Plaza hotel. Upon arrival, we were offered a free upgrade to a suite! Then, not knowing what to do, they happily took us to view both rooms to choose… with a smile. Incredible service upon stepping foot in the hotel! The lobby is very grand, and the rooms reflect the luxuriously rich atmosphere perfectly. Possibly the best bathroom I have ever seen, with an enormous waterfall shower, separate full sized deep bathtub, two sinks, separate toilet, and deadly so- an electronic weighing scale. The whole bathroom was almost the size of the bedroom, introduced by French windows. An absolute delight. Everything in the bedroom can be controlled electronically, and a nice touch was the iPod/iPhone docking station by the bed. The hotel can provide anything you want, from a kettle, to a mini-fridge (aside from your mini-bar so you can store your own drinks etc… ahem) We didn’t have a full length mirror though, which I’m sure they could have provided also. Nothing, however, is enough to take away the charm of the world’s most comfortable bed, crisp sheets and huggable pillows that envelope you after a hard day’s shopping. Speaking of which, they have an entire shopping centre underground, which is incredible! But if, like me, you don’t have $’000s to spend everyday, then it may not be the best place for your daily shopping fix. Especially as you are situated on 5th Avenue, which you must take full advantage of. Every morning, once you step out of the lift, you are greeted by fresh apples, international newspapers, and bottled Fiji water that you can take away with you. (Aside from the morning paper that is provided outside your bedroom door). The staff are always willing and eager to walk you around the hotel, and the concierge is at hand, recommending places to eat, drink and party. A BIG BUT! (not that kind… though you do find those around NY)… The GYM, situated in the basement, was disappointing- at best. It was small, with 1 treadmill, 1 cross trainer, and a couple of spinning bikes in a completely separate room that’s even smaller than the main gym! Worse still, it doesn’t offer any water… not even tap water. It’s shared with the residents and their one-on-one personal trainers, so you’ll have to get there very early to use any of the machines, or get some floor space. So! To avoid the claustrophobic atmosphere, just step across the road and run in Central Park.If it’s Sex And The City-meets-Big’s cheque book that you’re looking for, then the Plaza is for you. Located in one of the most prestigious addresses in Manhattan, the hotel offers a prime experience in New York, allowing you to weave your way through all the top shops and cafes by foot. I went on a girl’s holiday, and it will be something we will smile about for a long time to come.	
